WEBVTT

1
00:00:37.412 --> 00:00:39.414
[cell phone vibrating]

2
00:00:42.543 --> 00:00:44.336
- Hey. Teddi.
- There you are.

3
00:00:44.419 --> 00:00:45.796
Velma was starting to worry.

4
00:00:46.380 --> 00:00:47.673
<i>Ah. reception's been spotty.</i>

5
00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:48.841
[mouthing] It's Colter.

6
00:00:48.924 --> 00:00:50.342
Too spotty to return our texts?

7
00:00:50.425 --> 00:00:51.885
Did you tell him about
the Cobra?

8
00:00:51.969 --> 00:00:53.053
Here you go.

9
00:00:53.136 --> 00:00:54.816
[Teddi] Colter.
sent you a job. Stolen car.

10
00:00:54.847 --> 00:00:56.974
<i>Looks pretty straightforward
and a big payout.</i>

11
00:00:57.057 --> 00:00:59.101
Cascade. Idaho.
Vintage Shelby Cobra.

12
00:00:59.184 --> 00:01:00.245
Twenty thousand cash reward.

13
00:01:00.269 --> 00:01:01.371
Oh. so you do get our texts.

14
00:01:01.395 --> 00:01:03.315
You just choose not to
answer them. Good to know.

15
00:01:03.397 --> 00:01:05.691
<i>We need to know
if you're taking on a reward.</i>

16
00:01:05.774 --> 00:01:07.526
<i>so we can pull
a background for you.</i>

17
00:01:07.609 --> 00:01:08.819
<i>Put together the research.</i>

18
00:01:08.902 --> 00:01:11.238
Hey. Colter.
Word on the street is

19
00:01:11.321 --> 00:01:12.990
Billy is circling the job.

20
00:01:13.073 --> 00:01:14.074
- Great.
<i>- Thought you might</i>

21
00:01:14.157 --> 00:01:15.242
need a little motivation.

22
00:01:15.409 --> 00:01:17.661
Motivated. I'm gonna grab
a quick bite.

23
00:01:17.744 --> 00:01:20.122
I should be
in Cascade by 2:30.

24
00:01:32.467 --> 00:01:34.654
[man] So we're definitely not
going back to the site. right?

25
00:01:34.678 --> 00:01:36.722
[man 2] No. No more jobs.
if they're not paying...

26
00:01:38.056 --> 00:01:39.336
Can I get you
anything else. hon?

27
00:01:39.391 --> 00:01:41.476
Just the check.
I'm sort of in a hurry.

28
00:01:41.560 --> 00:01:43.270
- Oh. Work or fun?
- Work.

29
00:01:43.353 --> 00:01:44.897
You know what they say
about that.

30
00:01:45.439 --> 00:01:46.799
[Tozer] What the hell
is she doing?

31
00:01:51.111 --> 00:01:53.113
Still handing out them flyers.

32
00:01:54.072 --> 00:01:56.366
Some people just don't get
the damn memo.

33
00:01:57.117 --> 00:01:58.118
Come on.

34
00:01:58.535 --> 00:02:00.162
- Something wrong?
- Hope not.

35
00:02:02.789 --> 00:02:04.041
I wouldn't get involved.

36
00:02:04.124 --> 00:02:05.626
[Tozer] Kira. get over here!

37
00:02:08.462 --> 00:02:09.630
Too late.

38
00:02:12.925 --> 00:02:14.718
{\an8}You need to quit with these.

39
00:02:14.801 --> 00:02:16.553
You're upsetting people
with this garbage.

40
00:02:16.637 --> 00:02:18.805
- She's gone.
- Is there a problem?

41
00:02:20.015 --> 00:02:21.808
Mind your own business. friend.

42
00:02:22.434 --> 00:02:26.104
Look. it's okay.
I don't want any trouble.

43
00:02:26.730 --> 00:02:29.191
Hey! Where are you going?
Don't turn your back on me.

44
00:02:31.109 --> 00:02:32.903
[Colter] Hey. man.
no need to throw things.

45
00:02:36.657 --> 00:02:38.325
Told you to leave it.

46
00:02:38.784 --> 00:02:39.928
Odds are.
if you were gonna pull that.

47
00:02:39.952 --> 00:02:41.152
you would have done it already.

48
00:02:45.040 --> 00:02:46.166
No.

49
00:02:46.250 --> 00:02:47.251
That yours?

50
00:02:54.007 --> 00:02:55.092
[sighs]

51
00:02:57.678 --> 00:02:59.304
You shouldn't have done that.

52
00:02:59.429 --> 00:03:01.640
Me and the boys will help you
put the spare on.

53
00:03:01.723 --> 00:03:03.851
make sure you leave
and don't come back.

54
00:03:03.934 --> 00:03:05.143
Put the knife away.

55
00:03:05.227 --> 00:03:06.228
Sure thing.

56
00:03:07.020 --> 00:03:08.564
[grunting] No. stop!

57
00:03:09.565 --> 00:03:10.649
[Kira] Please. stop!

58
00:03:13.402 --> 00:03:16.280
- [both grunting]
- No. stop!

59
00:03:21.994 --> 00:03:24.621
[straining] Enough. Enough.

60
00:03:25.998 --> 00:03:27.040
Enough.

61
00:03:28.041 --> 00:03:30.961
- [breathing heavily]
- [Tozer coughing]

62
00:03:56.361 --> 00:03:57.905
Just about ready.

63
00:04:05.329 --> 00:04:06.455
Something wrong?

64
00:04:07.497 --> 00:04:08.707
You've got quite an interesting

65
00:04:08.790 --> 00:04:10.000
collection of scars.

66
00:04:10.292 --> 00:04:12.836
Oh. yeah.
it's me and my brother.

67
00:04:12.920 --> 00:04:14.796
- Dumb kid stuff. you know.
- Kid stuff?

68
00:04:14.880 --> 00:04:15.881
- Yeah.
- Okay.

69
00:04:15.964 --> 00:04:17.174
I plead the Fifth.

70
00:04:18.592 --> 00:04:21.011
Got it. Messed up childhood.

71
00:04:21.094 --> 00:04:22.304
Been there. done that.

72
00:04:22.387 --> 00:04:23.764
I do not like to talk about it.

73
00:04:24.348 --> 00:04:27.559
Any other past medical issues.
Mr. Shaw?

74
00:04:27.643 --> 00:04:31.772
It's Colter. and no.
no. healthy as a horse.

75
00:04:31.855 --> 00:04:33.649
Well. it's gonna be
seven stitches.

76
00:04:33.732 --> 00:04:35.234
a little bit deeper
than I expected.

77
00:04:35.317 --> 00:04:37.117
Last chance to take me up
on local anesthetic.

78
00:04:37.444 --> 00:04:39.071
No. No. I'm good. Thanks.

79
00:04:39.154 --> 00:04:41.114
And you're one of those
'pain is good' types?

80
00:04:41.198 --> 00:04:43.617
No. Not at all. It's just
when it comes to recovery.

81
00:04:43.700 --> 00:04:45.970
there's a five percent gain of
function on superficial wounds

82
00:04:45.994 --> 00:04:48.205
that are treated
without local anesthetic.

83
00:04:49.248 --> 00:04:50.624
Or you just like pain.

84
00:04:50.707 --> 00:04:52.042
- Little jab.
- Mmm-hmm.

85
00:04:55.212 --> 00:04:57.130
- What do you do?
- I'm a rewardist.

86
00:04:57.214 --> 00:04:58.465
What is that?

87
00:04:58.549 --> 00:05:00.843
Well. when rewards are posted

88
00:05:00.926 --> 00:05:03.220
for missing people or objects.
I go get them.

89
00:05:03.428 --> 00:05:05.973
Oh. Well. that sounds made up.

90
00:05:06.723 --> 00:05:07.724
It is not.

91
00:05:09.935 --> 00:05:11.019
And you're here on a job?

92
00:05:11.520 --> 00:05:14.565
I wasn't. but I'm starting
to think I might be.

93
00:05:15.065 --> 00:05:16.567
Hold still. Last one.

94
00:05:19.236 --> 00:05:20.529
- Okay. Yep.
- Yeah?

95
00:05:27.995 --> 00:05:29.288
Speaking of which.

96
00:05:32.207 --> 00:05:33.834
what do you know about her?

97
00:05:34.877 --> 00:05:37.671
Um. just what everybody knows.

98
00:05:37.754 --> 00:05:39.089
- Mmm-hmm.
- A bit of a nomad

99
00:05:39.173 --> 00:05:41.550
traveling from town to town.
living in her van.

100
00:05:42.342 --> 00:05:44.553
A little bit like you.
from the sounds of it.

101
00:05:44.636 --> 00:05:46.638
Our little lake town is popular

102
00:05:46.722 --> 00:05:48.015
with these van life folks.

103
00:05:48.098 --> 00:05:50.726
So. Mia was here
and then she moved along.

104
00:05:51.768 --> 00:05:54.313
Except her sister thinks that
something happened to her.

105
00:05:55.480 --> 00:05:57.482
So Kira posts these
flyers around town.

106
00:05:57.566 --> 00:05:58.751
but some folks
don't like that either.

107
00:05:58.775 --> 00:06:00.503
because it gives the
impression that something bad

108
00:06:00.527 --> 00:06:01.987
might have happened here.

109
00:06:02.070 --> 00:06:03.655
That's not exactly the image

110
00:06:03.739 --> 00:06:05.908
that you want
to give to tourists.

111
00:06:05.991 --> 00:06:08.452
- and second homebuyers.
- What do you think?

112
00:06:09.119 --> 00:06:10.245
I think she...

113
00:06:13.916 --> 00:06:16.293
I think I would be careful
if I were you.

114
00:06:16.835 --> 00:06:20.005
People don't like strangers
asking a lot of questions.

115
00:06:20.130 --> 00:06:23.217
Oh. Good to know.

116
00:06:24.551 --> 00:06:26.720
Uh. thank you.

117
00:06:27.763 --> 00:06:29.264
You're welcome.

118
00:06:38.023 --> 00:06:41.318
- Hey. Hey. Kira.
- Colter Shaw.

119
00:06:41.818 --> 00:06:43.654
Are you all right?
I feel terrible that

120
00:06:43.737 --> 00:06:44.821
you got hurt 'cause of me.

121
00:06:44.905 --> 00:06:46.532
No. I'm fine.
That guy needed a lesson.

122
00:06:46.615 --> 00:06:47.991
Not the first time.

123
00:06:48.700 --> 00:06:51.119
{\an8}-So it has to do with this?
- My sister?

124
00:06:51.203 --> 00:06:52.763
- I'm pretty sure it does.
- [siren wails]

125
00:06:53.622 --> 00:06:54.623
[Colter] Hmm.

126
00:06:58.585 --> 00:07:00.087
- [Sheriff Gale] Mr. Shaw.
- Yeah.

127
00:07:01.463 --> 00:07:04.007
You see the need for this
dispute to go any further?

128
00:07:04.091 --> 00:07:06.718
No. No. I think we both got
our message across.

129
00:07:06.802 --> 00:07:10.472
- No reason for charges.
- Good. Less paperwork for me.

130
00:07:11.431 --> 00:07:13.725
So you don't get the wrong
impression of our little town.

131
00:07:13.809 --> 00:07:15.769
- I had your tire repaired.
- Thank you.

132
00:07:15.853 --> 00:07:17.813
I hope this didn't delay
your travels too much.

133
00:07:17.896 --> 00:07:19.648
Where did you say
you were on your way to?

134
00:07:19.731 --> 00:07:20.858
I didn't.

135
00:07:23.235 --> 00:07:25.362
Listen. Kira.
It's been three months.

136
00:07:25.445 --> 00:07:27.698
There's nothing to suggest
your sister stayed in town.

137
00:07:27.781 --> 00:07:29.366
She simply moved on.

138
00:07:29.825 --> 00:07:31.535
Like she tended to do.

139
00:07:31.618 --> 00:07:32.938
like she did
a dozen times before.

140
00:07:33.412 --> 00:07:35.455
I know that's not
what you want to hear.

141
00:07:35.539 --> 00:07:36.582
but it's the truth.

142
00:07:37.541 --> 00:07:39.459
I'll keep that in mind. Sheriff.

143
00:07:39.543 --> 00:07:41.628
Maybe it's best
you moved on. too.

144
00:07:42.421 --> 00:07:44.464
Safe travels. Mr. Shaw.

145
00:07:48.594 --> 00:07:50.262
Have a wonderful day. Sheriff.

146
00:07:54.224 --> 00:07:55.309
Jackass.

147
00:07:57.728 --> 00:08:01.023
- Make you a cup of coffee?
- Sure.

148
00:08:07.821 --> 00:08:09.531
[Colter] Careful. That's hot.

149
00:08:10.741 --> 00:08:11.783
"Tucumcari."

150
00:08:12.784 --> 00:08:15.537
I was there for a job once.
Missing hydrologist.

151
00:08:15.621 --> 00:08:18.373
Did you find him?
The hydrologist?

152
00:08:18.457 --> 00:08:19.708
I did.

153
00:08:21.084 --> 00:08:22.502
Tell me about your sister.

154
00:08:22.586 --> 00:08:23.629
She was a drifter.

155
00:08:24.504 --> 00:08:26.548
Going from town to town.

156
00:08:26.632 --> 00:08:29.009
Backcountry skiing.
rock climbing.

157
00:08:29.092 --> 00:08:31.720
living out of a gross old van.

158
00:08:32.513 --> 00:08:34.640
I kept telling her
to stop running.

159
00:08:34.723 --> 00:08:35.763
What was she running from?

160
00:08:35.807 --> 00:08:38.393
Our childhood was...

161
00:08:39.645 --> 00:08:41.438
How shall I say. uh...

162
00:08:42.481 --> 00:08:44.942
Intense. A mess.

163
00:08:45.734 --> 00:08:47.611
We both
dealt with it differently.

164
00:08:47.694 --> 00:08:51.031
I know something about that.
Go on.

165
00:08:51.114 --> 00:08:53.450
She ran off and became
an adrenaline junkie.

166
00:08:53.534 --> 00:08:55.244
and I went to law school.

167
00:08:55.410 --> 00:08:58.247
Why are you so sure
she didn't just move on

168
00:08:58.330 --> 00:08:59.540
like the sheriff said?

169
00:08:59.915 --> 00:09:01.017
Well. the last time we spoke.

170
00:09:01.041 --> 00:09:02.751
she said she was going to Moab.

171
00:09:02.876 --> 00:09:04.545
I checked. she wasn't there.

172
00:09:04.628 --> 00:09:05.855
and there was
no sign of her in between.

173
00:09:05.879 --> 00:09:09.299
Nothing. This is the last
place anyone saw her.

174
00:09:09.883 --> 00:09:11.969
You check her socials?
Bank cards?

175
00:09:12.052 --> 00:09:14.113
It's hard for someone to just
up and disappear these days.

176
00:09:14.137 --> 00:09:15.931
Yeah. Nothing.

177
00:09:21.937 --> 00:09:23.730
What do you think
happened to her?

178
00:09:25.148 --> 00:09:27.734
Maybe she went somewhere
she shouldn't have.

179
00:09:27.818 --> 00:09:30.779
Shot her mouth off to
the wrong guy? I don't know.

180
00:09:30.863 --> 00:09:32.614
Like my new friend
back at the diner?

181
00:09:33.407 --> 00:09:34.658
Tom Tozer.

182
00:09:34.741 --> 00:09:36.177
He seemed pretty upset
about the flyers.

183
00:09:36.201 --> 00:09:37.428
Yeah. I think he knows something

184
00:09:37.452 --> 00:09:39.288
about Mia's disappearance.

185
00:09:39.371 --> 00:09:41.874
He and his buddies. they work
for the Winslow family.

186
00:09:41.957 --> 00:09:42.958
Tell me about them.

187
00:09:43.083 --> 00:09:45.669
They're trying to turn the
place into a resort town.

188
00:09:46.169 --> 00:09:48.755
Lakefront developments.
vacation condos.

189
00:09:51.675 --> 00:09:52.718
Can you help me?

190
00:09:53.468 --> 00:09:54.720
It is what I do.

191
00:09:56.054 --> 00:09:58.432
The reward is $5000.
It's not much.

192
00:09:58.515 --> 00:10:00.309
I collect only in success.

193
00:10:02.102 --> 00:10:03.312
I'll do everything I can

194
00:10:03.395 --> 00:10:05.355
to find out what happened
to your sister.

195
00:10:05.898 --> 00:10:07.417
I need you to know.
in cases like this.

196
00:10:07.441 --> 00:10:10.194
because she hasn't
made contact in so long.

197
00:10:10.277 --> 00:10:13.030
the odds of what I would call
a "good outcome."

198
00:10:14.698 --> 00:10:15.699
they're not favorable.

199
00:10:17.701 --> 00:10:19.036
You mean dead?

200
00:10:21.163 --> 00:10:22.873
I've made peace with that.

201
00:10:22.956 --> 00:10:25.834
If I can't have Mia back.
at least I'll have the truth.

202
00:10:29.588 --> 00:10:30.672
[sighs]

203
00:10:30.797 --> 00:10:32.525
Do you know where she was
last living in her van?

204
00:10:32.549 --> 00:10:35.844
Yeah. This piece of land
that the Winslows own.

205
00:11:33.402 --> 00:11:35.320
[cell phone vibrating]

206
00:11:40.367 --> 00:11:42.160
Bobby Exley. After hours.

207
00:11:42.828 --> 00:11:44.621
- What?
- Friday after 6:00.

208
00:11:44.705 --> 00:11:47.374
Surge rates apply. Like Uber.

209
00:11:47.457 --> 00:11:48.792
<i>I'm a growing business. Colter.</i>

210
00:11:48.917 --> 00:11:50.794
<i>"Beep." Means you're surging.</i>

211
00:11:50.878 --> 00:11:53.171
Mia Stine. Springland. Idaho.

212
00:11:53.255 --> 00:11:55.674
<i>Twenty-two. Sister says she's
been living out of a van.</i>

213
00:11:55.757 --> 00:11:57.885
<i>Disappeared three months ago.</i>

214
00:11:57.968 --> 00:12:00.137
Oof. I don't like vans.
let alone live in one.

215
00:12:00.637 --> 00:12:04.308
I got a Sleep Number. blackout
shades. and an ionizer.

216
00:12:04.391 --> 00:12:05.851
Sleep like a king.

217
00:12:06.560 --> 00:12:08.353
Looking for an '84
passenger van.

218
00:12:10.272 --> 00:12:13.066
[Bobby] I see the flyer here
with the license plate number.

219
00:12:13.150 --> 00:12:15.235
<i>I just sent you a photo
of an IMEI number</i>

220
00:12:15.319 --> 00:12:16.695
<i>off the back of a game camera.</i>

221
00:12:16.778 --> 00:12:18.138
- Take a look. will you?
- [clanging]

222
00:12:20.032 --> 00:12:21.700
Something's up.
I'll call you back.

223
00:12:21.783 --> 00:12:24.203
You gonna make me
come in there and get ya?

224
00:12:24.286 --> 00:12:25.537
[gun cocks]

225
00:12:33.298 --> 00:12:36.676
You ain't too smart. are ya?
Should've left town already.

226
00:12:36.760 --> 00:12:38.470
I'd be gone
if you hadn't stabbed me.

227
00:12:38.553 --> 00:12:40.054
I can do a hell of
a lot worse now.

228
00:12:40.138 --> 00:12:42.348
You're trespassing
on private land.

229
00:12:42.432 --> 00:12:44.142
Stand-your-ground law applies.

230
00:12:45.310 --> 00:12:46.644
So the Winslows
put you in charge

231
00:12:46.728 --> 00:12:49.063
of threatening anybody
who trespasses?

232
00:12:49.147 --> 00:12:50.190
Like Mia Stine.

233
00:12:50.273 --> 00:12:51.513
I don't know what Kira told you.

234
00:12:52.192 --> 00:12:53.610
but her sister was trouble.

235
00:12:54.235 --> 00:12:55.838
If you go poking around.
folks aren't going to

236
00:12:55.862 --> 00:12:57.655
like that very much.

237
00:12:58.823 --> 00:13:00.950
{\an8}Yeah. Yeah.
I got that already.

238
00:13:03.411 --> 00:13:04.611
{\an8}Look. man. I just came out here

239
00:13:04.662 --> 00:13:06.015
{\an8}to try to get
some answers for Kira.

240
00:13:06.039 --> 00:13:07.600
{\an8}Okay? Now. I'm not sure
that's an offense

241
00:13:07.624 --> 00:13:09.292
{\an8}that merits you shooting me.
[chuckles]

242
00:13:11.002 --> 00:13:13.463
{\an8}What are you? Some kind of PI?

243
00:13:13.546 --> 00:13:15.882
{\an8}No. No. no.
I collect reward money.

244
00:13:16.841 --> 00:13:19.219
{\an8}Kira's offered a reward for
information about her sister.

245
00:13:19.302 --> 00:13:21.096
{\an8}She's been missing a few months.

246
00:13:21.179 --> 00:13:22.806
{\an8}You really think
you can find her?

247
00:13:22.889 --> 00:13:24.265
{\an8}I don't know.

248
00:13:24.349 --> 00:13:26.327
{\an8}What do you have against
this missing girl. anyway?

249
00:13:26.351 --> 00:13:29.562
{\an8}It's not just her.
it's all these van life dopes.

250
00:13:30.105 --> 00:13:32.190
{\an8}They park their vans.
throw a party.

251
00:13:32.273 --> 00:13:33.900
{\an8}make a mess on company land.

252
00:13:33.983 --> 00:13:36.111
{\an8}My job is to move them off.

253
00:13:36.194 --> 00:13:38.071
{\an8}-What did you do?
- Nothing.

254
00:13:38.488 --> 00:13:41.074
{\an8}Maybe we exchanged
a few words. But that's all.

255
00:13:41.866 --> 00:13:46.204
{\an8}So then then why get so
worked up over Kira

256
00:13:46.287 --> 00:13:47.747
{\an8}Look. I got a wife and kids.

257
00:13:47.831 --> 00:13:49.499
{\an8}How do you think
it makes them feel?

258
00:13:49.582 --> 00:13:51.393
{\an8}Kira's asking folks in town
if I had something to do

259
00:13:51.417 --> 00:13:52.877
{\an8}with her sister disappearing.

260
00:13:52.961 --> 00:13:54.129
{\an8}I get that.

261
00:13:54.212 --> 00:13:57.841
{\an8}The crazy thing is. Mia made
such a big deal about her van.

262
00:13:58.508 --> 00:14:00.844
{\an8}Half the time.
she wasn't even in it.

263
00:14:00.927 --> 00:14:02.053
What do you mean?

264
00:14:02.137 --> 00:14:05.181
I came down here a few times
to try to negotiate.

265
00:14:05.265 --> 00:14:08.560
It turns out.
she wasn't sleeping there.

266
00:14:11.229 --> 00:14:12.355
Where was she sleeping?

267
00:14:12.814 --> 00:14:14.107
Hell if I know.

268
00:14:16.317 --> 00:14:17.694
[Teddi] Hey. Colter.

269
00:14:18.194 --> 00:14:20.447
- Where are you?
- Still in Springland.

270
00:14:21.114 --> 00:14:23.032
{\an8}I bet Velma
you'd still be there.

271
00:14:23.116 --> 00:14:24.826
{\an8}even though
you should be in Cascade

272
00:14:24.909 --> 00:14:27.912
{\an8}<i>looking for that stolen car</i>
<i>with a $20.000 reward.</i>

273
00:14:27.996 --> 00:14:29.539
{\an8}I need you
to look into someone for me.

274
00:14:29.622 --> 00:14:32.000
{\an8}It's a missing woman
by the name of Mia Stine.

275
00:14:32.083 --> 00:14:33.251
{\an8}Part of a van life group.

276
00:14:36.379 --> 00:14:39.299
{\an8}All right. Hey.
I might have something.

277
00:14:39.841 --> 00:14:41.384
{\an8}Rock climbing.

278
00:14:41.468 --> 00:14:43.228
{\an8}Oh. there's some cute
photos on this website.

279
00:14:43.303 --> 00:14:45.054
{\an8}I'll send them.

280
00:14:45.138 --> 00:14:47.348
{\an8}<i>There is a guy with her.</i>

281
00:14:47.557 --> 00:14:50.185
{\an8}-He's labeled "Gecko."
- [Teddi chuckles]

282
00:14:50.351 --> 00:14:51.436
{\an8}It's not "labeling."

283
00:14:51.519 --> 00:14:53.119
{\an8}When it's online.
they call it "tagging."

284
00:14:53.521 --> 00:14:54.522
Sorry.

285
00:14:55.023 --> 00:14:56.566
Hey. Velma.
where was this photo taken?

286
00:15:04.032 --> 00:15:06.159
You going for a
double figure eight knot?

287
00:15:06.576 --> 00:15:07.786
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

288
00:15:08.203 --> 00:15:10.288
Oh. Here you go.

289
00:15:10.371 --> 00:15:11.664
- Thanks.
- Sure.

290
00:15:13.291 --> 00:15:15.084
Hey. you know a climber up here.

291
00:15:15.168 --> 00:15:16.544
goes by the name of Gecko?

292
00:15:17.378 --> 00:15:19.130
Yeah. I know Gecko.

293
00:15:19.214 --> 00:15:20.673
Right up there.

294
00:15:20.840 --> 00:15:22.467
[Gecko grunts]

295
00:15:25.804 --> 00:15:26.930
Thanks.

296
00:15:31.518 --> 00:15:34.479
- Gecko!
- What's up?

297
00:15:34.562 --> 00:15:36.606
I need to talk to you
about Mia Stine.

298
00:15:38.525 --> 00:15:39.651
[Gecko clears throat]

299
00:15:40.944 --> 00:15:42.362
What about?

300
00:15:42.445 --> 00:15:45.615
Well. I was hoping
you'd come down.

301
00:15:47.992 --> 00:15:50.453
Nah. man. You come up.

302
00:15:57.710 --> 00:16:00.130
[soft rock music playing]

303
00:16:08.972 --> 00:16:11.182
I know. eating alone.
Don't judge.

304
00:16:11.266 --> 00:16:13.017
I do it more often
than not myself.

305
00:16:13.518 --> 00:16:15.770
- How did you find me?
- Trade secret.

306
00:16:16.396 --> 00:16:17.397
I need a favor.

307
00:16:18.231 --> 00:16:19.899
Okay. as long as
it doesn't involve

308
00:16:19.983 --> 00:16:21.568
taking out your stitches early.

309
00:16:22.152 --> 00:16:24.737
No. You. uh...

310
00:16:28.074 --> 00:16:29.200
You know who that is?

311
00:16:31.661 --> 00:16:33.788
- It's Matt Winslow.
- Winslow.

312
00:16:34.873 --> 00:16:36.458
As in. Winslow Resorts?

313
00:16:37.709 --> 00:16:39.437
You think Matt Winslow
had something to do with

314
00:16:39.461 --> 00:16:40.462
Mia's disappearance?

315
00:16:42.422 --> 00:16:43.462
I know they were together.

316
00:16:43.506 --> 00:16:44.716
In what capacity. I don't know.

317
00:16:46.885 --> 00:16:49.888
Well. I know he had some
troubles over the years.

318
00:16:49.971 --> 00:16:53.433
Um... Fights and shoplifting.
I think.

319
00:16:53.516 --> 00:16:55.351
Um. I remember
my old boss saying

320
00:16:55.435 --> 00:16:57.395
that his mom was always worried

321
00:16:57.479 --> 00:16:59.022
about something or another.

322
00:16:59.105 --> 00:17:02.358
and his father telling him
that he had to toughen up.

323
00:17:04.986 --> 00:17:06.863
I shouldn't even be
telling you that much.

324
00:17:06.946 --> 00:17:07.947
Okay. It's all right.

325
00:17:08.031 --> 00:17:09.791
I can get the rest from
his criminal history.

326
00:17:10.158 --> 00:17:13.995
Nope. There won't be much.
His dad employs half the town.

327
00:17:14.078 --> 00:17:15.789
so charges usually get dropped.

328
00:17:16.790 --> 00:17:19.626
Nobody from around here wants
to go after the Winslows.

329
00:17:20.001 --> 00:17:21.961
Least of all the sheriff.

330
00:17:22.045 --> 00:17:24.339
Well. it's a good thing
I'm not from around here.

331
00:17:25.090 --> 00:17:26.091
Where are you from?

332
00:17:26.800 --> 00:17:28.218
A place you never heard of.

333
00:17:28.301 --> 00:17:30.220
Echo Ridge.
Sierra National Forest.

334
00:17:30.470 --> 00:17:32.806
Oh. Sounds remote.

335
00:17:32.889 --> 00:17:35.058
You could say that.
Yeah. Yeah.

336
00:17:36.351 --> 00:17:37.936
Well. thanks for the info. Doc.

337
00:17:38.019 --> 00:17:39.020
It's Beth.

338
00:17:39.979 --> 00:17:44.943
And Colter from Echo Ridge
in the Sierra National Forest.

339
00:17:47.028 --> 00:17:48.113
you owe me a drink.

340
00:17:49.531 --> 00:17:50.824
I'll see what I can do.

341
00:17:53.118 --> 00:17:54.160
Thank you.

342
00:18:12.762 --> 00:18:14.097
[doorbell rings]

343
00:18:15.223 --> 00:18:17.934
- [man on intercom] <i>Yeah?</i>
- My name is Colter Shaw.

344
00:18:18.017 --> 00:18:20.770
I'm looking for a
Matt Winslow. aka Gecko?

345
00:18:24.065 --> 00:18:25.108
Come on. Matt.

346
00:18:25.191 --> 00:18:26.544
you're gonna have to
talk to me at some point.

347
00:18:26.568 --> 00:18:28.278
It might as well be now.

348
00:18:31.030 --> 00:18:32.740
[car engine starting]

349
00:18:38.955 --> 00:18:40.915
[tires screeching]

350
00:18:42.250 --> 00:18:43.960
[Colter] No. we're not
doing this again.

351
00:18:44.961 --> 00:18:46.004
The disappearing?

352
00:18:58.060 --> 00:18:59.144
What do you want?

353
00:19:00.938 --> 00:19:02.898
Mia's sister. Kira.
she's got a few questions

354
00:19:02.981 --> 00:19:04.042
about what happened
to her sister.

355
00:19:04.066 --> 00:19:05.067
And I wish I knew.

356
00:19:05.150 --> 00:19:07.820
If you don't know. why'd you
bail on me at the rock wall?

357
00:19:11.198 --> 00:19:13.283
- [scoffs]
- Nobody in this town

358
00:19:13.367 --> 00:19:14.928
seems to want to talk
about what happened to Mia.

359
00:19:14.952 --> 00:19:16.346
And I really don't know
what to tell you.

360
00:19:16.370 --> 00:19:18.330
Well. the truth would be nice.

361
00:19:18.414 --> 00:19:19.790
She important to you?

362
00:19:22.876 --> 00:19:23.877
Yeah.

363
00:19:24.545 --> 00:19:26.296
- You were in a relationship?
- We were.

364
00:19:27.381 --> 00:19:29.234
Look. man. I really don't
wanna talk about this.

365
00:19:29.258 --> 00:19:30.259
No one does.

366
00:19:31.969 --> 00:19:33.721
If you ever really
cared about her. Matt.

367
00:19:33.804 --> 00:19:35.055
look. all I'm trying to do

368
00:19:35.139 --> 00:19:36.419
is find out
what happened to her.

369
00:19:38.809 --> 00:19:40.018
She left.

370
00:19:40.978 --> 00:19:42.038
Okay? One minute.
we're talking

371
00:19:42.062 --> 00:19:43.480
about hitting the road together.

372
00:19:43.564 --> 00:19:45.441
next. she tells me
she wants to go it alone.

373
00:19:45.524 --> 00:19:46.525
You ask her why?

374
00:19:46.608 --> 00:19:48.610
She didn't give me the chance.

375
00:19:48.694 --> 00:19:52.197
Just left a note.
and then poof. Ghosted me.

376
00:19:54.658 --> 00:19:55.993
How did she feel
about this town?

377
00:19:56.076 --> 00:19:57.077
I don't know.

378
00:19:57.161 --> 00:19:59.121
I guess she kind of just
saw it for what it was.

379
00:19:59.580 --> 00:20:00.914
Plus. she had a lot of opinions.

380
00:20:00.998 --> 00:20:02.082
wasn't afraid to share 'em.

381
00:20:02.166 --> 00:20:05.335
It was actually one of
the things I dug about her.

382
00:20:07.629 --> 00:20:10.049
It didn't make her too popular
with some folks.

383
00:20:10.132 --> 00:20:13.218
so she was tired of being
hassled and she skipped.

384
00:20:13.719 --> 00:20:14.720
I get it.

385
00:20:18.265 --> 00:20:19.808
Do you still have that note?

386
00:20:20.684 --> 00:20:22.394
[Matt] I told you.
man. that's it.

387
00:20:23.187 --> 00:20:24.313
It's such a Mia move.

388
00:20:24.980 --> 00:20:26.940
She liked drama. Big gestures.

389
00:20:27.024 --> 00:20:28.442
Fighting for what
she believed in.

390
00:20:28.525 --> 00:20:29.526
[Colter] Mmm.

391
00:20:29.610 --> 00:20:32.738
- Did she have a temper?
- That's one way of puttin' it.

392
00:20:33.280 --> 00:20:35.074
[vehicle approaching]

393
00:20:36.408 --> 00:20:38.410
Oh. Parents.

394
00:20:46.418 --> 00:20:47.669
Hey. Matt.

395
00:20:49.338 --> 00:20:50.714
- What's going on?
- Hey. Dad.

396
00:20:50.798 --> 00:20:53.384
- Who's this?
- Name's Colter Shaw.

397
00:20:53.550 --> 00:20:56.136
Ah. I've heard about you.
Mr. Shaw.

398
00:20:56.220 --> 00:20:57.513
I was just asking your son here

399
00:20:57.596 --> 00:20:58.889
a few questions about Mia Stine.

400
00:20:58.972 --> 00:21:00.599
The girl who went missing?

401
00:21:01.058 --> 00:21:03.060
Why would you be asking
our son about her?

402
00:21:03.143 --> 00:21:04.853
Not a big deal. Mom.

403
00:21:04.978 --> 00:21:07.106
Hung out a bit.
Hit Deaver's wall a few times.

404
00:21:07.189 --> 00:21:08.190
Just casual.

405
00:21:08.273 --> 00:21:10.734
Mr. Shaw. I'd advise you
to speak to Sheriff Gale.

406
00:21:11.151 --> 00:21:12.152
We met.

407
00:21:12.236 --> 00:21:15.155
Hmm. Then you know what
sort of crowd she ran with.

408
00:21:15.239 --> 00:21:16.466
I just wanted see
if Matt knew anything

409
00:21:16.490 --> 00:21:17.783
about her disappearance.

410
00:21:18.367 --> 00:21:19.368
Ah.

411
00:21:19.618 --> 00:21:21.161
He obviously doesn't.

412
00:21:21.787 --> 00:21:24.706
Look. as I'm sure
Sheriff Gale told you.

413
00:21:25.999 --> 00:21:28.168
the sister's just trying
to cause trouble.

414
00:21:28.836 --> 00:21:30.254
Thanks for the info. Matt.

415
00:21:38.554 --> 00:21:40.681
Anything we can give Colter
on Matt Winslow?

416
00:21:40.764 --> 00:21:43.475
Actually. I had my friend Lou
run a background check.

417
00:21:43.559 --> 00:21:45.769
Lou from the pet shelter?

418
00:21:45.853 --> 00:21:47.730
He does background checks
for adoptions.

419
00:21:47.813 --> 00:21:51.525
Great. Is Matt Winslow
a worthy pet foster candidate?

420
00:21:51.608 --> 00:21:54.153
That. I can't say.
He's had a few minor arrests.

421
00:21:54.236 --> 00:21:56.822
However. I checked
the local court dockets.

422
00:21:57.406 --> 00:22:00.617
Winslow Resorts has been
involved in a lot of lawsuits.

423
00:22:00.701 --> 00:22:01.910
What kind of suits?

424
00:22:02.745 --> 00:22:05.122
That I can't tell.
The complaints aren't online.

425
00:22:05.205 --> 00:22:06.290
[Teddi] Hmm.

426
00:22:06.373 --> 00:22:08.250
But I do know a legal genius
that we could send

427
00:22:08.333 --> 00:22:09.376
to the county courthouse.

428
00:22:09.460 --> 00:22:11.044
assuming she's in the area.
that is.

429
00:22:11.128 --> 00:22:13.922
Reenie Greene.
You read my mind.

430
00:22:14.590 --> 00:22:16.842
- But Colter...
- Can swallow his pride

431
00:22:16.925 --> 00:22:17.926
and trust me.

432
00:22:18.010 --> 00:22:19.011
Hmm.

433
00:22:20.471 --> 00:22:22.115
[Colter] Matt Winslow's been
holding onto that letter

434
00:22:22.139 --> 00:22:23.223
for months.

435
00:22:23.307 --> 00:22:24.683
She mention anything about him?

436
00:22:24.767 --> 00:22:26.143
- No.
- No?

437
00:22:26.643 --> 00:22:28.645
This is a page
from her climbing journal.

438
00:22:32.191 --> 00:22:33.334
but that is not her handwriting.

439
00:22:33.358 --> 00:22:34.860
Let's take a look.

440
00:22:35.986 --> 00:22:36.987
No. it's not.

441
00:22:37.654 --> 00:22:39.740
[cell phone vibrating]

442
00:22:41.825 --> 00:22:43.035
Bobby. Good news?

443
00:22:43.118 --> 00:22:44.703
I think I found Mia's van.

444
00:22:45.412 --> 00:22:47.039
Now you're speaking
my language. Where?

445
00:22:47.122 --> 00:22:49.666
Turns out the ID on that
game camera you snagged.

446
00:22:49.750 --> 00:22:51.001
not the only one.

447
00:22:51.794 --> 00:22:54.588
Winslows have them networked
all over their properties.

448
00:22:54.671 --> 00:22:56.632
I got a decent look
at the perimeter.

449
00:22:56.715 --> 00:22:58.175
but I think I got her van going

450
00:22:58.258 --> 00:22:59.578
to one of the
Winslow's properties

451
00:22:59.635 --> 00:23:01.154
right around the time
of her disappearance.

452
00:23:01.178 --> 00:23:03.931
<i>The funny thing is.
it never came back out.</i>

453
00:23:04.014 --> 00:23:06.975
Sending you the location now.

454
00:23:07.059 --> 00:23:08.659
- Nice work.
<i>- It was actually kind of fun.</i>

455
00:23:09.103 --> 00:23:11.397
The cams use what we call
IoT connectivity tech.

456
00:23:12.398 --> 00:23:15.526
You tap into the matrix. which
not everybody can handle.

457
00:23:15.609 --> 00:23:16.735
let alone navigate.

458
00:23:17.277 --> 00:23:18.421
You know. one of these days.
I'm gonna lay

459
00:23:18.445 --> 00:23:19.571
the observer effect on you.

460
00:23:19.655 --> 00:23:20.989
- Can't wait.
- We're livin' in

461
00:23:21.073 --> 00:23:22.366
a simulation. C.

462
00:23:22.449 --> 00:23:24.201
<i>Better get used to it now.</i>

463
00:23:24.284 --> 00:23:25.661
<i>I. uh. gotta go.
Gotta go. Bobby.</i>

464
00:23:30.707 --> 00:23:33.460
Mia's van was found
on Winslow family land.

465
00:23:38.090 --> 00:23:40.718
- Let's get you home.
- No. I'm coming.

466
00:23:40.801 --> 00:23:44.680
I can tell you immediately
if it's her van or her body.

467
00:23:49.518 --> 00:23:51.687
There's no talking you
out of this. is there?

468
00:23:51.770 --> 00:23:52.813
No.

469
00:23:54.606 --> 00:23:55.607
Okay.

470
00:24:10.831 --> 00:24:13.625
All right. The van entered
from here. which means...

471
00:24:19.923 --> 00:24:22.009
- What is it?
- Stay close. They got cameras.

472
00:24:22.092 --> 00:24:23.093
[Kira] Okay.

473
00:24:28.348 --> 00:24:29.349
[Colter] That's it.

474
00:24:30.934 --> 00:24:32.436
Can you do this?

475
00:24:33.937 --> 00:24:36.356
Yeah. I'm good.

476
00:24:38.192 --> 00:24:39.943
Looks like
it's been here a while.

477
00:24:52.206 --> 00:24:53.957
[Kira]
That's definitely her van.

478
00:25:06.720 --> 00:25:08.555
- [gunshot]
- Get down! Get down!

479
00:25:09.473 --> 00:25:13.268
Breathe. Look at me.
Just breathe.

480
00:25:16.605 --> 00:25:17.606
[Kira] Oh. my God.

481
00:25:19.066 --> 00:25:22.069
- We're going to run for it.
- What? Are you crazy?

482
00:25:22.152 --> 00:25:24.405
Odds are f they wanted to
kill us. we'd be dead already.

483
00:25:24.488 --> 00:25:26.365
- How do you know that?
- Trust me.

484
00:25:28.826 --> 00:25:30.911
- See that shed?
- [Kira] Yeah.

485
00:25:30.994 --> 00:25:32.496
Great. That's where
we're going.

486
00:25:32.579 --> 00:25:34.081
- On three.
- Okay.

487
00:25:34.164 --> 00:25:37.167
One. two. three. Let's go.

488
00:25:37.251 --> 00:25:39.044
- [GUNSHOT]
- Run! Run. run. run!

489
00:25:39.128 --> 00:25:40.337
[Kira shrieks]

490
00:25:42.172 --> 00:25:43.757
- [Colter] Come on.
- [gasps] My arm.

491
00:25:43.841 --> 00:25:45.050
I got you. Come on.

492
00:25:48.053 --> 00:25:49.388
[groans]

493
00:25:51.515 --> 00:25:52.516
[Colter] You okay?

494
00:25:54.351 --> 00:25:56.145
It's not bad.

495
00:25:57.020 --> 00:25:58.480
- There we go. Come on.
- Okay.

496
00:26:16.710 --> 00:26:18.253
We're good.
We weren't followed.

497
00:26:19.212 --> 00:26:20.464
Who the hell is shooting at us?

498
00:26:22.632 --> 00:26:23.901
Someone doesn't want us
looking into

499
00:26:23.925 --> 00:26:25.594
your sister's disappearance.

500
00:26:25.677 --> 00:26:28.138
Loosen that for me. will you?
Let me see the cut.

501
00:26:28.221 --> 00:26:30.349
Mia. The van.

502
00:26:38.273 --> 00:26:39.441
Hold that corner.

503
00:26:41.568 --> 00:26:43.695
All right. you can move
that now.

504
00:26:45.280 --> 00:26:46.323
[sniffles]

505
00:26:48.367 --> 00:26:49.701
When I saw the van.

506
00:26:50.452 --> 00:26:52.621
part of me was still
holding on to hope.

507
00:26:55.374 --> 00:26:59.002
I loved my sister.
but I never told her.

508
00:27:01.713 --> 00:27:04.132
All I did was tell her
that she was wasting her life.

509
00:27:05.384 --> 00:27:07.678
She shouldn't run
from her problems.

510
00:27:11.932 --> 00:27:13.475
I know that kind of regret.

511
00:27:15.352 --> 00:27:16.687
Does it ever go away?

512
00:27:20.232 --> 00:27:21.233
No.

513
00:27:24.236 --> 00:27:28.490
But you learn to keep it
with you as a reminder

514
00:27:28.573 --> 00:27:30.409
of what that person
meant to you.

515
00:27:32.911 --> 00:27:34.913
Good. bad.
It... It doesn't matter.

516
00:27:36.373 --> 00:27:37.457
They helped make you.

517
00:27:38.375 --> 00:27:39.710
I like that.

518
00:27:43.505 --> 00:27:48.301
All right. Uh...

519
00:27:48.385 --> 00:27:49.821
While I do that.
you're gonna see a doctor

520
00:27:49.845 --> 00:27:50.971
about that cut. okay?

521
00:27:52.681 --> 00:27:53.682
Okay.

522
00:27:57.936 --> 00:28:00.313
Around here. landowners are
within their rights

523
00:28:00.397 --> 00:28:01.815
to shoot at trespassers.

524
00:28:01.898 --> 00:28:02.899
Right over here.

525
00:28:07.112 --> 00:28:08.196
What the hell?

526
00:28:08.280 --> 00:28:10.657
Don't know what kind of game
you're playing at. Mr. Shaw.

527
00:28:10.741 --> 00:28:13.035
- Somebody moved it.
- Maybe Bigfoot moved it.

528
00:28:13.118 --> 00:28:15.495
Somebody shot at us
to scare us off.

529
00:28:15.579 --> 00:28:17.706
Like I said. seeing as how
you were trespassing.

530
00:28:17.789 --> 00:28:19.916
you're lucky the Winslows
don't press charges.

531
00:28:20.000 --> 00:28:21.477
Now you're gonna
get back in your truck

532
00:28:21.501 --> 00:28:23.086
and you're gonna
leave this town.

533
00:28:23.170 --> 00:28:24.504
You did your best for that girl.

534
00:28:24.588 --> 00:28:26.131
but her sister is long gone.

535
00:28:26.214 --> 00:28:28.425
And I expect you to be
long gone. too.

536
00:28:38.435 --> 00:28:39.978
[line ringing]

537
00:28:40.937 --> 00:28:42.206
[Bobby] <i>Dude. it's the middle</i>
<i>of the night.</i>

538
00:28:42.230 --> 00:28:43.458
<i>You think I work
all the damn time?</i>

539
00:28:43.482 --> 00:28:45.817
- I'm sorry. You're sleeping?
- I'm at work.

540
00:28:47.152 --> 00:28:49.088
Are you still hooked up to
that network of game cameras?

541
00:28:49.112 --> 00:28:50.572
The ones that found
the van for us?

542
00:28:50.655 --> 00:28:52.282
- I can be.
<i>- Good.</i>

543
00:28:52.366 --> 00:28:53.992
<i>I need you to find out
who moved it.</i>

544
00:28:58.372 --> 00:28:59.414
Bobby. I got to go.

545
00:29:10.717 --> 00:29:12.010
[Reenie gasps]

546
00:29:13.095 --> 00:29:15.555
Really. Colter?
Put that thing away.

547
00:29:15.639 --> 00:29:16.848
Reenie. what the hell?

548
00:29:16.932 --> 00:29:18.225
A man dumb enough to hide a key

549
00:29:18.308 --> 00:29:19.588
in the same place
for three years

550
00:29:19.643 --> 00:29:21.853
shouldn't even be allowed
to carry one of those.

551
00:29:29.695 --> 00:29:31.905
You know.
it takes most people days

552
00:29:31.988 --> 00:29:33.156
to get this much information.

553
00:29:33.240 --> 00:29:35.701
so you're lucky
that I was close by.

554
00:29:35.784 --> 00:29:37.452
I trust that Teddi
explained to you

555
00:29:37.536 --> 00:29:38.829
that I was already in the area.

556
00:29:38.912 --> 00:29:40.914
taking a deposition
on another case.

557
00:29:40.997 --> 00:29:43.834
You know. the kind that
pays me what I'm worth.

558
00:29:44.960 --> 00:29:48.130
- I appreciate you. Reenie.
- Appreciate and admire?

559
00:29:51.466 --> 00:29:52.926
- What is all this?
- [chuckles]

560
00:29:53.885 --> 00:29:57.347
All right. This is about
two dozen lawsuits.

561
00:29:57.431 --> 00:29:59.266
Some settled. some active.

562
00:29:59.349 --> 00:30:00.559
Someone told you how everyone's

563
00:30:00.642 --> 00:30:02.102
scared of the Winslows. right?

564
00:30:02.185 --> 00:30:04.354
- Yeah.
- The Winslows sue people.

565
00:30:04.438 --> 00:30:07.774
For trespassing. for property
damage. breach of contract.

566
00:30:07.858 --> 00:30:09.484
- You name it.
- Okay. So?

567
00:30:09.568 --> 00:30:12.154
So. this one's different.

568
00:30:13.030 --> 00:30:15.198
For once. it's the Winslows
getting sued.

569
00:30:15.282 --> 00:30:17.367
A case brought by
Nathaniel Orcutt.

570
00:30:17.492 --> 00:30:19.077
They wanted to buy
his lakefront parcel.

571
00:30:19.161 --> 00:30:21.830
He said no.
Then crazy coincidence.

572
00:30:21.913 --> 00:30:23.290
his barn burns down.

573
00:30:24.249 --> 00:30:25.689
The county declined
to bring charges.

574
00:30:25.751 --> 00:30:27.794
So Mr. Orcutt
sued the Winslow family

575
00:30:27.878 --> 00:30:30.213
for civil harassment
and property damages.

576
00:30:30.297 --> 00:30:31.965
- Did he win?
- Didn't get the chance.

577
00:30:32.049 --> 00:30:35.510
Three weeks after filing suit.
Mr. Orcutt died.

578
00:30:36.928 --> 00:30:38.138
Huh. No cause of death.

579
00:30:38.221 --> 00:30:39.306
No. there is not.

580
00:30:39.389 --> 00:30:40.807
And look here.

581
00:30:42.309 --> 00:30:44.603
Orcutt's lawyer was required
to disclose the witnesses

582
00:30:44.686 --> 00:30:47.898
he intended to call.
Anything look familiar?

583
00:30:49.191 --> 00:30:51.485
Mia Stine was gonna testify
against the Winslows?

584
00:30:51.568 --> 00:30:53.288
That's what we call
circumstantial evidence.

585
00:30:53.362 --> 00:30:55.082
- [cell phone chimes]
- We're gonna need more.

586
00:30:56.782 --> 00:30:58.116
Something from Bobby.

587
00:31:02.788 --> 00:31:03.872
Will this work?

588
00:31:03.955 --> 00:31:06.083
- [Reenie] Hmm.
- Yeah? All right.

589
00:31:06.917 --> 00:31:07.918
All right.

590
00:31:08.877 --> 00:31:10.504
Wait. Where are you going?

591
00:31:10.587 --> 00:31:12.427
To have another conversation
with Matt Winslow.

592
00:31:13.215 --> 00:31:14.633
Not without your lawyer.

593
00:31:15.342 --> 00:31:17.719
[soft music playing]

594
00:31:24.434 --> 00:31:25.644
You again.

595
00:31:27.187 --> 00:31:29.189
- And who the hell is this?
- I'm a lawyer.

596
00:31:29.272 --> 00:31:30.941
People usually
pay me for counsel.

597
00:31:31.024 --> 00:31:33.068
but I'll give you
this one for free.

598
00:31:33.610 --> 00:31:34.611
You're screwed.

599
00:31:35.904 --> 00:31:37.131
Dude. I told you
everything I know.

600
00:31:37.155 --> 00:31:38.949
No. I don't think that you did.

601
00:31:41.243 --> 00:31:43.203
Mia Stine never left this town.

602
00:31:43.286 --> 00:31:44.329
That's not true.

603
00:31:44.413 --> 00:31:46.289
- I found her van.
- On a Winslow property.

604
00:31:49.126 --> 00:31:50.627
You didn't know. did you?

605
00:31:50.711 --> 00:31:53.505
Mia was preparing to testify
against your father's company.

606
00:31:53.588 --> 00:31:55.590
- I can't talk about this.
- Why not?

607
00:31:55.674 --> 00:31:56.717
Hmm?

608
00:31:57.801 --> 00:31:58.802
[Matt grunts softly]

609
00:31:58.885 --> 00:32:01.471
Matt. I'm gonna really
need you to concentrate here.

610
00:32:02.973 --> 00:32:04.182
It's over.

611
00:32:04.266 --> 00:32:07.019
If you ever cared about Mia.
you tell the truth now.

612
00:32:07.978 --> 00:32:09.271
Do right by her.

613
00:32:14.151 --> 00:32:16.820
- I told her I...
- You told her. told her what?

614
00:32:20.490 --> 00:32:22.284
Told her what your father
was up to?

615
00:32:22.367 --> 00:32:25.203
Intimidating landowners.
burning down buildings.

616
00:32:25.287 --> 00:32:27.039
snatching up land
for his lakefront empire.

617
00:32:27.122 --> 00:32:29.458
Yeah. And I couldn't
stand it anymore.

618
00:32:29.541 --> 00:32:31.543
I wanted her to see
that I wasn't like him.

619
00:32:31.626 --> 00:32:32.919
And why is that?

620
00:32:35.130 --> 00:32:37.215
You were helping your family
do these things?

621
00:32:37.299 --> 00:32:39.634
Mia found out.
asked you to say something.

622
00:32:39.718 --> 00:32:40.719
Take a stand.

623
00:32:44.097 --> 00:32:45.349
She just wouldn't drop it.

624
00:32:45.932 --> 00:32:47.684
It's my fault. isn't it?

625
00:32:47.768 --> 00:32:49.478
Shouldn't have said anything.

626
00:32:49.561 --> 00:32:50.896
I should have just lied to her.

627
00:32:52.773 --> 00:32:56.151
[sighs] You burned down
Nathaniel Orcutt's place?

628
00:32:56.735 --> 00:32:57.986
No. I didn't.

629
00:32:58.779 --> 00:33:00.072
But I was there
when it happened.

630
00:33:00.155 --> 00:33:01.948
and I knew it was wrong.

631
00:33:07.120 --> 00:33:08.246
Who did it?

632
00:33:10.957 --> 00:33:12.793
Come on. Matt.

633
00:33:13.877 --> 00:33:14.878
Give me a name.

634
00:33:20.175 --> 00:33:23.220
Tony. Works for my parents.

635
00:33:23.303 --> 00:33:25.722
Driver. Does other things.

636
00:33:25.806 --> 00:33:26.848
You told Mia this?

637
00:33:30.143 --> 00:33:31.144
I loved her.

638
00:33:32.813 --> 00:33:34.815
I told her that we could
get out of here together.

639
00:33:34.898 --> 00:33:37.317
just hit the road. just be
done with all of this crap.

640
00:33:37.401 --> 00:33:38.485
Oh. but let me guess.

641
00:33:38.568 --> 00:33:40.487
She went and told
Mr. Orcutt instead.

642
00:33:40.570 --> 00:33:43.156
She promised to him
that she would testify

643
00:33:43.240 --> 00:33:44.342
to everything that she knew.

644
00:33:44.366 --> 00:33:45.784
and she wanted me
to do the same.

645
00:33:45.867 --> 00:33:47.494
Me? I was too scared
of my dad.

646
00:33:47.577 --> 00:33:48.870
Mia wasn't scared. though.

647
00:33:48.954 --> 00:33:50.706
She was never scared
of anything.

648
00:33:51.289 --> 00:33:52.791
And that's it?
That's what happened?

649
00:33:52.874 --> 00:33:54.268
She just all of a sudden.
out of the blue.

650
00:33:54.292 --> 00:33:55.585
broke up with you?

651
00:33:55.669 --> 00:33:57.462
- You believe that?
- It's what happened.

652
00:33:57.546 --> 00:33:58.714
I think she was disgusted

653
00:33:58.797 --> 00:33:59.983
that I wouldn't
stand up to them.

654
00:34:00.007 --> 00:34:01.216
so she bailed.

655
00:34:01.299 --> 00:34:03.343
Oh. come on. man.
you're smarter than that.

656
00:34:04.052 --> 00:34:05.595
Somebody else wrote the note.

657
00:34:09.474 --> 00:34:12.144
- [Matt chuckles] No.
- [Colter] No?

658
00:34:12.227 --> 00:34:13.687
No. No. my dad
wouldn't do that.

659
00:34:13.770 --> 00:34:15.290
My dad wouldn't have
gotten her killed.

660
00:34:15.647 --> 00:34:16.773
No? All right. well.

661
00:34:18.442 --> 00:34:19.818
Yeah. take a look at that.

662
00:34:20.777 --> 00:34:22.446
What does that look like. huh?

663
00:34:22.571 --> 00:34:25.240
Because to me. that looks like
Tony in the woods.

664
00:34:25.949 --> 00:34:28.785
moving Mia's van.

665
00:34:30.162 --> 00:34:31.621
Why is he doing that?

666
00:34:34.249 --> 00:34:35.250
There you go. Run away.

667
00:34:35.333 --> 00:34:37.478
Hide behind your parents
like you have your whole life.

668
00:34:37.502 --> 00:34:40.172
That's great. The only problem
with that. Matt.

669
00:34:40.839 --> 00:34:43.216
is that sick feeling
in your gut right now?

670
00:34:43.800 --> 00:34:45.385
That's not going anywhere.

671
00:34:46.178 --> 00:34:48.180
Not until the truth comes out.

672
00:35:06.743 --> 00:35:07.744
Tony.

673
00:35:19.297 --> 00:35:21.174
I thought Sheriff Gale
told you to leave town.

674
00:35:21.257 --> 00:35:22.485
Yeah. he did.
but I couldn't leave

675
00:35:22.509 --> 00:35:23.927
without finishing the job.

676
00:35:24.010 --> 00:35:25.929
Not sure what you're trying
to pull here. Shaw.

677
00:35:26.012 --> 00:35:27.013
What is this. Matt?

678
00:35:27.096 --> 00:35:28.473
I'll take care of it. Charlotte.

679
00:35:28.556 --> 00:35:29.682
Tony. if you wouldn't mind

680
00:35:29.766 --> 00:35:31.392
escorting these folks
off our property

681
00:35:31.476 --> 00:35:33.937
- while I call the sheriff.
- Oh. I already called him.

682
00:35:34.020 --> 00:35:35.021
Matt. get over here now!

683
00:35:37.899 --> 00:35:39.818
- Let him go.
- Tony. right?

684
00:35:40.360 --> 00:35:42.695
You should've killed me
at the van. Tony.

685
00:35:42.779 --> 00:35:43.780
What was the plan?

686
00:35:43.863 --> 00:35:45.406
To scare us off?
Get rid of the van?

687
00:35:45.782 --> 00:35:47.325
Have the sheriff
chase us out of town?

688
00:35:48.117 --> 00:35:50.370
I've no idea
what you're talking about.

689
00:35:50.954 --> 00:35:52.664
The van. Tony.
The one you just removed

690
00:35:52.747 --> 00:35:53.790
from the property.

691
00:35:53.873 --> 00:35:56.167
- Did you kill Mia. huh? Why?
- Easy. easy.

692
00:35:56.251 --> 00:35:57.502
That's enough.

693
00:35:59.003 --> 00:36:01.673
- [Tony grunts]
- Get outta here.

694
00:36:02.382 --> 00:36:03.925
What did you tell him to do?

695
00:36:04.884 --> 00:36:06.928
No one killed Mia.

696
00:36:08.054 --> 00:36:11.224
All we did was firmly request
that she move along.

697
00:36:11.307 --> 00:36:12.701
Yeah. but she never
moved along. did she?

698
00:36:12.725 --> 00:36:13.726
That's enough. Shaw.

699
00:36:13.810 --> 00:36:15.329
You had Mia killed
because she found out

700
00:36:15.353 --> 00:36:17.021
what your boys did
to Mr. Orcutt.

701
00:36:17.105 --> 00:36:18.731
That's after they
burned down his barn.

702
00:36:18.815 --> 00:36:20.775
She was a witness.
She could have brought down

703
00:36:20.859 --> 00:36:23.194
your whole situation.
so you couldn't let her live.

704
00:36:23.611 --> 00:36:25.864
Is this is some kind of joke?

705
00:36:25.947 --> 00:36:29.492
All we did was get her
to leave town.

706
00:36:30.910 --> 00:36:32.579
- Right. honey?
- Yes.

707
00:36:33.997 --> 00:36:35.456
But again.
she didn't leave. did she?

708
00:36:35.540 --> 00:36:36.708
I have no idea what she did.

709
00:36:36.791 --> 00:36:38.831
So her van just magically
appeared on your property?

710
00:36:38.877 --> 00:36:40.628
You're lying. Both of you.

711
00:36:48.011 --> 00:36:49.179
He's not.

712
00:36:55.560 --> 00:36:56.561
Mom?

713
00:36:59.147 --> 00:37:01.024
[Eric] Charlotte.
what did you do?

714
00:37:02.817 --> 00:37:04.903
You owe your son the truth.

715
00:37:05.945 --> 00:37:07.625
You couldn't have him
running off with Mia.

716
00:37:07.655 --> 00:37:08.966
Not after she found out
what your family

717
00:37:08.990 --> 00:37:10.450
does to people
that get in the way.

718
00:37:10.533 --> 00:37:13.578
So what?
You just got rid of her.

719
00:37:14.412 --> 00:37:15.830
And you lied to your son.

720
00:37:17.040 --> 00:37:18.541
I was only trying to tell him.

721
00:37:18.625 --> 00:37:22.420
warn him what she was going
to do if she kept talking.

722
00:37:22.504 --> 00:37:25.215
So you got Tony to make sure
she couldn't talk.

723
00:37:29.093 --> 00:37:31.888
- Why?
- Don't say anything.

724
00:37:31.971 --> 00:37:32.972
Mom?

725
00:37:35.975 --> 00:37:38.228
This girl wouldn't stop.

726
00:37:39.020 --> 00:37:40.063
She wouldn't leave.

727
00:37:40.897 --> 00:37:43.525
I tried and tried to make
her see. but she wouldn't.

728
00:37:43.608 --> 00:37:45.401
So you killed her.

729
00:37:47.111 --> 00:37:49.948
[siren wailing]

730
00:38:08.591 --> 00:38:11.636
- [cell phone vibrating]
- Hey. Teddi.

731
00:38:12.387 --> 00:38:14.747
- What the hell is that sound?
- [Teddi] It's a pottery wheel.

732
00:38:15.223 --> 00:38:17.684
which I'm trying. so Velma

733
00:38:17.767 --> 00:38:19.519
will leave me alone
and we can return it.

734
00:38:21.020 --> 00:38:23.106
[chuckles] What's next?

735
00:38:23.648 --> 00:38:25.608
Well. we're looking
into a few things.

736
00:38:26.151 --> 00:38:28.069
Up in Bozeman.
there's a teenage runaway.

737
00:38:28.153 --> 00:38:29.654
Hey. Teddi. give the man a rest.

738
00:38:31.447 --> 00:38:33.741
Oh. that's Reenie.
I should probably say bye.

739
00:38:34.200 --> 00:38:35.326
Yeah. you should.

740
00:38:41.583 --> 00:38:44.961
Hey. By the way.
I'll be filing a civil suit

741
00:38:45.044 --> 00:38:47.046
on behalf of Nathaniel
Orcutt's next of kin.

742
00:38:47.130 --> 00:38:48.590
So you could
help me out with that.

743
00:38:48.673 --> 00:38:50.383
Sure. Sure.

744
00:38:50.800 --> 00:38:51.801
Good job on this.

745
00:38:51.885 --> 00:38:53.678
Mia's body was recovered

746
00:38:53.761 --> 00:38:55.513
on one of the Winslows'
other properties.

747
00:38:55.597 --> 00:38:56.681
I owe you one.

748
00:38:56.764 --> 00:38:58.391
I'll add it to your
very long tab.

749
00:38:58.892 --> 00:39:00.059
[mouthing] Okay.

750
00:39:00.185 --> 00:39:02.687
Oh. almost forgot.
I got a weird call.

751
00:39:02.770 --> 00:39:04.606
Some guy Russell?
Says he knows you.

752
00:39:04.689 --> 00:39:05.833
I have no idea why he called me

753
00:39:05.857 --> 00:39:06.917
or how he even got my number.

754
00:39:06.941 --> 00:39:08.318
